thread_title: "Almost" Relationships
post_content: It's a norm these days; yung mga no label, no strings attached, etc. Why do you think this kind of relationship is prevalent and being accepted in this generation?

thread_title: "Almost" Relationships
post_content: Because people nowadays simply don't care or it's not as important as it used to be. People do what they want and don't want to be bothered or inconvenienced by those things anymore.

thread_title: "Almost" Relationships
post_content: Nothing to worry about ts.. this type of relationship has been around for a very long time. In the past the only people who can engage in this type of relationship are those in very active social circles... Usually the rich.. Today, thank god for the internet, we can have sex with as many people we find interesting. Tumabla lang tayo sa mga mayayaman..

thread_title: "Almost" Relationships
post_content: ^ hmm interesting sa exp ko wala naman akong napansin na prevalent yang practice na yan nung formative years ko and my parents (are) and mingles with socialites,,rich people but not mega filthy rich. but I do got wind sometimes of extra marital affairs within or of some of them in their circle. iba na nga ngayon. mabilis ma influenced at mag evolve ang kabataan gawa nam innernet. fb ginagawang dating site. am daming giriian na nangyayari between opposite and same sexes

thread_title: "Almost" Relationships
post_content: Instant gratification coupled with restlessness and lack of patience. Habang masaya, game pa rin. Pero once na bore na, nagsawa na, hindi na fun, hahanap na ng iba. And having no labels make that easier to do.
quoted_post: It's a norm these days; yung mga no label, no strings attached, etc. Why do you think this kind of relationship is prevalent and being accepted in this generation?

thread_title: "Almost" Relationships
post_content: Always do what makes you happy... Stay away from stressors of the world... In short pag andyan na ang conflict, people these days find it easy to quit and move on just like that...

thread_title: Love Letter to A PExer
post_content: Dear Ate "Mandy", Since wala naman akong kalandian sa PEX, ikaw na lang gagawan ko ng letter for this V-day. You are one of the cool peeps here if only people would have known how cool you really are in many ways. Nakakaaliw mga kwento mo in many things kahit papano. Nakakagising din sa mga boring na hapon kahit bihirang-bihira lang tayo mag-usap. Alam ko naman na minsan wala ka lang talagang choice at ako lang online sa pagkarami mong options. Basta wag kalimutan ang pasalubong na pinangako mo. Also, thanks sa mga tips about life/love/work/workingout. Kahit papaano many of them are helpful in many ways. I think. You are one of my trusted "ate" or big sister na me tiwala naman ako pagkwentuhan ng kung anu-anong kagaguhan. Haha! Lastly, paki-bawas-bawasan ang pagiging praning or paranoid mo sa madaming bagay. Ibuhos mo na lang sa squats yan. Hihi Uma-ate-zoned, Joby
